text: Franklin Delano Roosevelt High School is a public high school located in the United States. It serves students in grades 9-12. It is a zoned high school, with around 3,700 students and it has 280,717 sq ft of space. It was established in 1965. It was named after Franklin Delano Roosevelt, the 32nd President of the United States, who served from 1933 to 1945. The school is located in New York City, New York. It has a large campus with various facilities, including classrooms, science labs, a library, a gymnasium, and outdoor sports fields. == References == Category:High schools in New York (state)
